223	/// buffer on the LuaState (signalling that a `coroutine.wrap` body is
224	/// running synchronously on the main thread), append the arguments into
225	/// that buffer and return 0 values without suspending. The wrapped
226	/// function continues to run; `aux_wrap` dispenses the buffered values one
227	/// per call. If no buffer is active we fall through to the faithful
228	/// `lua_yieldk` translation, which on the main thread surfaces the C-Lua
229	/// "attempt to yield from outside a coroutine" error.
