1285	    /// `lua_sethook` clears the mask whenever the hook is uninstalled, so a
1286	    /// non-zero mask is equivalent to a non-NULL `L->hook` for the
1287	    /// `debug.gethook` call site. Avoids invoking `state.hook()`, which is
1288	    /// still a Phase-B `todo!` on `LuaState`.
